solution: ```class Solution {
    public String largestPalindrome(int n, int k) {
        if (k == 1) return "9".repeat(n);
        StringBuilder sb = new StringBuilder();
        int half = (n + 1) / 2;
        for (int i = 0; i < half; i++) sb.append('9');
        String left = sb.toString();
        long num = Long.parseLong(left);
        while (true) {
            String cand = buildPalindrome(num, n);
            if (Long.parseLong(cand) % k == 0) return cand;
            num--;
        }
    }
    private String buildPalindrome(long left, int n) {
        String s = Long.toString(left);
        String rev = new StringBuilder(s).reverse().toString();
        if ((n & 1) == 1) rev = rev.substring(1);
        return s + rev;
    }
}
```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(10^(n/2))
space complexity: O(n)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: Start with the largest possible half of the palindrome (all 9s), mirror it to form the full palindrome, and decrement until the number is divisible by k. The loop runs at most 10^(n/2) times, which is feasible because k ≤ 9 and the first valid candidate is usually found quickly.

